Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and quarter @button mushrooms{4%ounce}. Halve @sweet potato{1}(halved and sliced into 1/4-inch-thick half-moons). Toss veggies on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp}; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack, flipping halfway through, until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

While veggies roast, trim and quarter @Persian cucumber{1}(trimmed and sliced into 1/4-inch-thick pieces). In a small #bowl{}, combine @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, 1 TBSP water, @sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Stir in cucumber. Set aside to pickle.

> For 4 servings, use 1 tsp sugar and 2 TBSP water.

Gently massage @microwavable black rice{1} in package to break up grains. Partially open package; season with salt and add @butter{1%TBSP}. Microwave for ~{90%seconds}. Fluff with a #fork{}.

> TIP: For easier fluffing, transfer rice to a bowl first.

Place @butter{1%TBSP} in a second small #microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Stir in @miso sauce concentrate{1} and @sugar{1/4%tsp}.

Once roasted veggies are done, carefully transfer to a large bowl. Drizzle with miso butter and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}. Place kale in a second large bowl and drizzle with @sesame dressing{1.5%ounce}. Season lightly with salt. Massage kale until leaves soften.

Add rice, half the roasted veggies, and half the pickled cucumber (draining first) to bowl with kale; divide between shallow bowls or plates. Top with remaining roasted veggies and remaining pickled cucumber to taste. Serve.